  "explanation": "The defendant committed a significant breach of trust in their professional capacity as an accountant, having embezzled $25,000 to satisfy personal debts. In determining the sentence, the court took into account several mitigating factors, including the defendant's lack of a prior criminal record and the fact that restitution has already commenced through partial repayment of the funds. While the breach of fiduciary duty warrants incarceration as a deterrent, the defendant’s proactive steps toward making the victim whole and their clean history justify a sentence at the lower end of the guidelines. The outburst from the courtroom spectator was entirely disregarded as it bears no relevance to the legal merits of the case.",
  "verdict": 6
}
